WEBVTT

00:04:29.419 --> 00:04:32.285
I just said, "I don't know
what I'm doing."

00:04:33.381 --> 00:04:35.373
And then we just sat there in silence --

00:04:35.397 --> 00:04:36.998
just ... silence.

00:04:39.123 --> 00:04:41.382
Before he got up to get ready
for his own match,

00:04:41.406 --> 00:04:42.922
he gave me this piece of advice

00:04:42.946 --> 00:04:45.544
that would change the entire
direction of my life.

00:04:45.568 --> 00:04:49.784
He told me the best wrestlers
are just themselves, but "turned up."

00:04:51.058 --> 00:04:54.438
He said successful wrestlers
find the traits within themselves

00:04:54.462 --> 00:04:55.780
they're the strongest at

00:04:55.804 --> 00:04:58.669
and make those the focus
of who they become in the ring.

00:04:59.902 --> 00:05:01.361
So there I sat --